[conversation_undertaker]
{
	[text*]
	{
		order = 0;
		choice = more;
		screen_text = "The Lich lord sent you to seek the Chalice of Mourning, didn't he?\n\nThe Fire King seems to know you are coming if this blistering heat is any indication. I never dreamed it would come to this. I wish I had never spoken to the Fire King that lonely evening.";
	  f scroll_rate = 6.500000;
	}
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "He knew all too well that I alone could travel into the tombs. I should have known it was a trick. He said he could use it to make Gwendolyn love me. He forged the pendant from it for her to wear, but she never loved me; she just got taken away and nearly killed. She will never love me now.\n\nI don't know if you can undo what I have done, but if you do, I will be content to live out my days never meddling in the affairs of the gods again, and let the Imperial Tombs fall to dust at my passing. Perhaps this is written somehow.";
	  f scroll_rate = 6.500000;
	}
}
[conversation_queen]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I am sorry I misjudged you, outlander. I was too absorbed in my study to realize that the Fire King had been scheming against all of us. He has always been possessive, but we used to keep each other in balance. His power now grows unchecked with every passing moment.\n\nI will use what little power I have left to keep these good people alive, if you are brave enough to put the Fire King in his place before his greed spills over into the world around us.";
	  f scroll_rate = 6.500000;
	}
}
[conversation_captain]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = shop;
		screen_text = "We're in a bad way now friend.\n\nBy the looks of it, the Fire King aims to take this whole valley by force, and without my men, I frankly don't think we stand a chance. They don't want to negotiate, and if the weapons they bear are any indication of what is yet to come, our days are numbered.\n\nLucky for you we looted some pretty good gear off the last few waves of Krug that came through. If you are of the mind to go talk to the King, you are going to need them worse than us.";
	  f scroll_rate = 6.500000;
	}
}
[conversation_gwendolyn]
{
	[text*]
	{
		choice = shop;
		screen_text = "I made it back alive, thanks to you, and not a moment too soon either. I just hope we can settle things with the Fire King before I run out of potions.\n\nSo much greed in the valley these days... I was as much a victim of my own greed as the Undertaker was of his, I can't blame him for that.\n\nMayor Gilwin said you are the only one who can help us now. I saved my biggest vials for you if you need them, it is the least I could do for our savior.";
	  f scroll_rate = 6.500000;
	}
}
